article.headline: Coastal Carolina 70, Wright State 63
article.story: CONWAY, S.C. (AP) -- Jack Leasure scored 22 points, including four in the second overtime period, to lead Coastal Carolina to a 70-63 win against Wright State. Coastal (1-2) also got 20 points and 11 rebounds from Moses Sonko and 12 points and 14 rebounds from Joseph Harris. The game was tied at 28 at the half, 51 at the end of regulation and 55 at the end of the first overtime period. Coastal put together an 11-3 run at the start of the second overtime period to put the game away. Wright State (1-1) was led by Vaughn Duggins with 12 points and five rebounds. Jordan Pleiman and DaShaun Wood, who fouled out with 40 seconds left in regulation, each had 11 points. Pleiman grabbed a team-high 10 rebounds and had four assists.
